In [3]:
def define_columns(df, birth_time, death_time):
    group_labels = set(df.columns) - set((birth_time, death_time))
    id_col = [i for i in group_labels if "id" in i and df[i].dtype == "int"]
    for i in id_col:
        group_labels.remove(i)
    return group_labels, id_col

#@snoop
def check_adequacy(df):
    for col in df.columns:
        if df[col].dtype == 'object':
            try:
                df[col] = pd.to_datetime(df[col])
            except ValueError:
                pass
    return df

def bin_column(data, columns):
    for i in group_labels:
        if len(data[i].unique) > 6:
            if data[i].dtype == "object":
                n_unique = len(data[i].unique)
                n_bins = int(
                    input(
                        f"     : {n_unique},   object"
                    ))
                data[i] = pd.cut(data[i], bins=n_bins, ordered=False)
            if data[i].dtype == "int":
                n_unique = len(data[i].unique)
                n_bins = int(
                    input(
                        f"     : {n_unique},   - int"
                    ))
                data[i] = pd.cut(data[i], bins=n_bins, ordered=True)

    return data

#@eye
def calculate_interval(data):
    values = [data.loc[i] for i in data.index]
    var = np.var(values)
    length = len(values)
    left_bound = np.mean(values) - var / np.sqrt(length)
    right_bound = np.mean(values) + var / np.sqrt(length)
    interval = f"{left_bound} - {right_bound}"
    return str(interval)
In [46]:
def make_cohorts(data, birth_time, death_time):
    observ_period = data[death_time].max() - data[death_time].min()
    if 1 <= observ_period.days <= 100:
        freq = "7D"
    elif 100 <= observ_period.days <= 400:
        freq = "1M"
    else:
        freq = "3M"
    cohorts = (data.set_index(birth_time).sort_index().groupby(
        pd.Grouper(freq=freq))[["lifetime"]].mean())
    return cohorts

# @eye
@logger.catch
def make_vintage(dataframe, birth_time, death_time):
    data = dataframe.copy()
    bt, dt = birth_time, death_time
    group_labels, id_col = define_columns(data, bt, dt)
    data["birth_hour"] = data[birth_time].apply(lambda x: x.hour)
    data["day_part"] = pd.cut(data["birth_hour"],
                              bins=3,
                              labels=["night", "morning", "day"],
                              ordered=True)
    data["lifetime"] = (data[death_time].sub(
        data[birth_time])).apply(lambda x: (x.total_seconds() / 3600))

    data["day"] = data[birth_time].apply(lambda x: x.dayofyear)
    grouped_tables = [
        data.groupby(["day", "day_part", i])[["lifetime"]].agg(np.mean)
        for i in group_labels
    ]
    grouped_tables.append(data.groupby(["day", "day_part"])[id_col].count())
    grouped_tables.append(
        data.groupby(["day", "day_part"])[["lifetime"]].agg([np.mean]))
    # grouped_tables.append(data)
    grouped_tables.append(make_cohorts(data))
    for table in grouped_tables:
        table.dropna(inplace=True)
        table = table.reset_index()
    return grouped_tables

#@snoop
def calculate_retention(data, group):
    retention = defaultdict(float)
    for i, j in list(
            product(data['id_port'].unique(), data['lifetime'].unique())):
        retention[(i,
                   j)] = sum(data[data[group] == i]["lifetime"] >= j) / data[
                       data[group] == i].shape[0]
    #retention = pd.DataFrame(pd.Series(retention), columns=['Retention']).sort_values(by='Retention', ascending=False).T
    return pd.DataFrame(retention, index=['Retention'])

# @snoop
def calculate_lifetime(retention, group):
    lts = defaultdict(float)
    for j in data[group].unique():
        group_retention = sorted(np.array(retention.unstack(0)[j]))[:-1]
        lt = 0
        for i in range(len(group_retention)):
            if i not in (0, len(group_retention) - 1):
                lt += group_retention[i]
            else:
                lt += group_retention[i] / 2
        lts[j] = lt
    return lts

# @eye
def visualize(data):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(20, 5))
    #calculate_retention(data).T.plot(ax=axes[0])
    (data.set_index("time_came").sort_index()[[
        "lifetime"
    ]].rolling("1d").mean()).plot(ax=axes, title="Lifetime Dynamic Overall")

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(20, 6))
    by_port = (data.pivot_table(index="time_came",
                                columns="id_port",
                                values="lifetime").rolling("1d").mean())
    for loc, col in zip(list(product(range(2), range(3))), by_port.columns):
        by_port[col].plot(ax=axes[loc], title=f"LT Dynamic in {col}")
    plt.tight_layout()

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,
                             len(data["day_part"].unique()),
                             figsize=(20, 6))
    by_dp = (data.pivot_table(index="time_came",
                              columns="day_part",
                              values="lifetime").rolling("1d").mean())
    for num, i in enumerate(data["day_part"].unique()):
        by_dp[i].plot(ax=axes[num], title=f"LT Dynamic {i}")

    plt.tight_layout()


visualize(data)
